            ">Push for the death penalty?</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.presidentialsummary.com/email/images/luigi-mangione-manhattan-state-supreme-court-arraignment-december.png" alt="Luigi Mangione at State Supreme Court in Manhattan for his arraignment in December" href="https://www.presidentialsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;"><i>Luigi Mangione at the State Supreme Court in Manhattan for his arraignment in December. Credits: Jefferson Siegel for The New York Times
            </i></p>
        </mj-text>
        
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">Attorney General Pam Bondi is directing federal prosecutors to <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #4D3060; color: black;" href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-03-04-2025-h1-1-seek-the-death-penalty?source=website" target="_blank">seek the death penalty</a> for Luigi Mangione if convicted of the December murder of UnitedHealthcare CEO Brian Thompson. Mangione faces federal charges, including murder through the use of a firearm, making him eligible for the death penalty.</p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">Bondi emphasized the decision aligns with President Trump's agenda to combat violent crime. Donald Trump <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #4D3060; color: black;" href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-03-04-2025-h1-2-restored-the-death-penalty?source=website" target="_blank">restored the death penalty</a> for all types of federal crimes after taking office, while Biden commuted the sentences of almost all federal death row inmates.</p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">Mangione’s defense attorney, Karen Friedman Agnifilo, condemned the decision, calling it "political" and going against local federal prosecutors' recommendations. Mangione has pleaded not guilty to state charges and has yet to enter a plea to federal charges. He is scheduled for a court appearance on April 18. </p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
