        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="TNYAdobeCaslonPro, 'Times New Roman', serif;" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="              
              font-size: 24px;
              line-height: 1.5;
              font-weight: 400;
              margin-top: 2px !important;">Italy tightens citizenship law</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.5"><strong>Summary: The Italian government is limiting citizenship to its descendants and making the requirements for dual citizenship harder.</strong></p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">According to the old rules, anyone who could prove their connection to Italian ancestors alive after March 17, 1861, was provided citizenship. However, Minister of Foreign Affairs Antonio Tajani said the system was outdated, and to prevent abuse, <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #4D3060; color: black;" href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-03-04-2025-h3-3-citizenship-had-to-be-limited?source=website" target="_blank">citizenship had to be limited</a> to descendants who have a real connection to a European nation.</p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">The new decree claims eligibility through ‘jus sanguinis,’ or the descendant bloodline route. The highlights of the decree include:</p>
          <ol style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5; margin-top:4px;margin-bottom:5px;">
            <li>The applicant should have at least one Italian parent or grandparent to be eligible for citizenship.
            </li>
            <li style="margin-top:5px;">Dual nationals may lose citizenship if they don’t engage by paying taxes, voting, or renewing their passport. 
            </li>
            <li style="margin-top:5px;">
            Italian consulates will no longer process citizenship applications. All applications will be processed centrally by the government. 
            </li>
          </ol>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">South Americans, particularly Argentines, took advantage of the old scheme, and since Trump took office, more people from the US have been looking into it. Many who claim Italian descent have been securing citizenship abroad. From 2014 to 2024, the number of Italians living abroad rose by 40%.</p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>

